    name: _tierNames[i],\n                price: _tierPrices[i],\n                totalCount: _tierCounts[i],\n                soldCount: 0,\n                startTokenId: startTokenId,\n                createdAt: block.timestamp\n            });\n\n            eventTierIds[eventId].push(tierId);\n\n            // Create seat mappings for each seat in this tier\n            for (uint256 j = 0; j < }\n\n        return ownedSeats;\n    }\n\n    // ========== ADMIN FUNCTIONS ==========\n\n    /**\n     * @notice Deactivate an event\n     * @param _eventId Event ID\n     */\n    function params.operator: Address that may be allowed to operate on tokens without being their owner.

params.receiver: Address to which tokens are being transferred.

ERC721InvalidSender(address).details: Indicates a failure with the token `sender`. Used in transfers.

params.sender: Address whose tokens are being transferred.
